There is nothing new about writing in plain language.  It was the style of Mark Twain, George Orwell, Ernest Hemingway, Winston Churchill and many others.  Notable judicial writers of this style have been Justice Oliver Wendell Holmes and Lord Denning.

\par {\listtext\pard\plain\s16 \f38\expnd0\expndtw-3\lang3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid8257942 \hich\af38\dbch\af0\loch\f38 13\tab}Rules for plain language were laid down at least as long ago as 1931, in the 3rd edition of Fowler's }{
