However, if the policy is so complex that it is impossible to keep the law simple and also precise, drafters should invite the policy-makers to consider expressing it in statements of general principl
e.  This can reduce detailed, specific provisions to very simple statements, but results in less certainty.  The policy-makers must decide in each case whether the lack of certainty is acceptable.  They must also decide the degree of generality to be used
.
\par {\listtext\pard\plain\s16 \f38\lang3081\langfe1033\langfenp1033\insrsid8257942 \hich\af38\dbch\af0\loch\f38 67\tab}If drafters take this approach, it is unnecessary to resolve the dispute whether general principles dr}{\expnd0\expndtw-3\insrsid8257942 
